                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <date>March 23/1853</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>My Dear Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am almost ashamed to address you in<lb/> reply to yours of such an\n                early date, but, believe me<lb/> sir, it is from no want of regard for your kind\n                attention<lb/> to me, neither is it from any disrespect to your correspon<lb/>dence,\n                far from it, for, although personally unacquainted<lb/> yet, from the tenor of your\n                letters, I feel satisfied, I could<lb/> too esteem you as a friend, and I have no\n                doubt that<lb/> the reasons I assign for my delay, will be ample apology<lb/> for\n                not replying to you at an earlier period, firstly,<lb/> I had to make preparations\n                in my school for a public<lb/> &amp; private examination, in which I am sure\n                you<lb/> will sympathize with me, (I have sent you the whole<lb/> particulars for\n                insertion in your Occident,) secondly,<lb/> though not least, I had to complete\n                arrangements for<lb/> my union with <persName>Mr. Sarfaty's</persName> daughter,\n                this completed<lb/> I will devote myself to your service. Should you feel<lb/>\n                disposed to appoint me your Agent, I shall most<lb/> readily render my aid in order\n                to forward your in-<lb/>terests, but I fear, as the state of things are, you\n                must<lb/> not expect great progress, as to all appearance we<lb/> are in a fallen\n                state, and very likely a just retribution<lb/> for the well known immorality\n                    <sic>practised</sic> here<lb/>\n                <add>Hebrew</add> I hear of no other country with<lb/> so little hope of success as\n                    <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>, the veil of <sic>dispair</sic><lb/> seems to\n                overshadow us, and a gloom hovers over<lb/> us, threatening the approach of some\n                impending<lb/> evil. I have been here about 9 years, but I have<lb/> not known\n                things to bear such a fearful aspect<lb/> as at present, 'tis true it affects me\n                little, but every<lb/> thing sooner or later must have its turn, and I fear<lb/> the\n                future, I will at any rate do my best for you</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3b56dr2w/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
