                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3b56dr2w/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p>let me know the state of your affairs in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>,<lb/> and\n                order to be handed over to me such Books<lb/> as you have in the possession of other\n                persons, I obtained<lb/> a Subscriber for you, and would have obtained more,\n                had<lb/> I been in possession of your authority, this was merely<lb/> in\n                conversation with <persName>Mr. Phenias Bravo</persName> on your<lb/> letter to\n                    <persName>Mr. Jacobs</persName>, which was the gem of the day<lb/> in\n                    <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>, I went up at <persName>Sollas'</persName> my\n                brother in law, to<lb/> operate at his child's b<add>Hebrew</add> and he was\n                delighted with<lb/> it, I think it a good incentive to your getting\n                sub-<lb/>scribers, but you must know more or less that we<lb/> have very few\n                literary characters here. I thank<lb/> you for the numbers you have sent me\n                gratuitously</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Miss Peixotto</persName> handed me your last<lb/>\n                correspondence enclosed in hers, when she was ex-<lb/>ceedingly ill, and indeed not\n                expected to live, she<lb/> has since recovered, and wrote a letter in reply<lb/> to\n                yours but not living in <placeName>Kingston</placeName> she left it at<lb/> her\n                brother's residence in <placeName>Spanish Town</placeName>, so<lb/> therefore she\n                has been unable to address you by<lb/> this conveyance. I have taken the\n                opportunity<lb/> of <persName>Mr. Hart's</persName> leaving for your part of the\n                world<lb/> being a large communication and would have cost<lb/> you a little extra\n                postage.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The financial condition of our<lb/> Synagogue is any thing but\n                prosperous, my income<lb/> is about $800 by both departments Assistant Reader<lb/>\n                &amp; School master, which taking all things into<lb/> consideration I would resign\n                tomorrow for the<lb/> same amt: either in <placeName>England</placeName> or\n                    <placeName>America</placeName> should<lb/> you hear of any thing you may let me\n                know</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3b56dr2w/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
